---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Web Management - Cody Smith" description="Managed WordPress hosting, security, updates, and monthly reporting. Your site lives on my infrastructure.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-40 pb-24 px-6 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[600px] h-[400px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <a href="/services" class="reveal inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-neutral-500 text-sm hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors duration-300 mb-8 group">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18" />
        </svg>
        All services
      </a>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="reveal text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em]">01</span>
        <div class="reveal gradient-divider flex-1"></div>
      </div>
      <h1 class="reveal font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl text-neutral-100 leading-[1.05] mb-6">
        Web Management
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-500 italic text-sm tracking-wide mb-10">Keep it running.</p>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Most businesses don't know who's hosting their site, whether it's secure, or what happens if something breaks. I change that. Your site moves onto infrastructure I control, and every month you get a report that proves it's taken care of.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Process</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">How it works.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="relative">
        <!-- Vertical line -->
        <div class="absolute left-6 md:left-8 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-gradient-to-b from-amber-500/40 via-amber-500/20 to-transparent"></div>

        <div class="space-y-16">
          <div class="reveal relative pl-16 md:pl-20">
            <div class="absolute left-3 md:left-5 top-1 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border-2 border-amber-500 bg-neutral-950 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-amber-400 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold">1</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-xl font-medium mb-3">Migration & onboarding</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
              I move your existing site onto my server. DNS, hosting, email routing, plugins, the whole thing. Zero downtime. Your site comes off whatever shared hosting it's on and onto dedicated cloud infrastructure I control. This is included in every engagement, not billed separately.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal relative pl-16 md:pl-20">
            <div class="absolute left-3 md:left-5 top-1 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border-2 border-amber-500/60 bg-neutral-950 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-amber-400/60 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold">2</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-xl font-medium mb-3">Baseline audit</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
              Once the site is on my infrastructure, I run a full health check. Plugin conflicts, outdated dependencies, security gaps, performance bottlenecks. Everything gets catalogued. This becomes your first Site Health Report and the baseline for all future measurement.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal relative pl-16 md:pl-20">
            <div class="absolute left-3 md:left-5 top-1 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border-2 border-amber-500/40 bg-neutral-950 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-amber-400/40 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold">3</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-xl font-medium mb-3">Ongoing management</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
              Monthly retainer kicks in. Updates are tested before they go live. Security monitoring runs 24/7. Backups happen daily. Uptime is tracked. When something breaks (and eventually something always does), I'm the one who gets the alert, not you.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="reveal relative pl-16 md:pl-20">
            <div class="absolute left-3 md:left-5 top-1 w-6 h-6 rounded-full border-2 border-amber-500/20 bg-neutral-950 flex items-center justify-center">
              <span class="text-amber-400/20 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold">4</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-xl font-medium mb-3">Monthly proof</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
              On the first of every month, you get a Site Health Report. What was updated, what was fixed, what's coming next, and how performance compares to last month. You never have to wonder if the work is getting done. The report proves it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What's included -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 dot-grid">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Coverage</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">What's included.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 reveal-stagger">
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:0">
          <div class="text-amber-400 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M5 12h14M5 12a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2v4a2 2 0 01-2 2M5 12a2 2 0 00-2 2v4a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">Cloud hosting</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Dedicated cloud server. Not shared with hundreds of other sites. Fast, isolated, and fully under my control.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:1">
          <div class="text-amber-400 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">Security monitoring</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">SSL certificates, firewall configuration, malware scanning, and login hardening. Problems caught before you know they exist.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:2">
          <div class="text-amber-400 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">Updates</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">WordPress core, themes, and plugins, tested in staging before going live. No "update all and hope" approach.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:3">
          <div class="text-amber-400 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M4 7v10c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4V7M4 7c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4M4 7c0-2.21 3.582-4 8-4s8 1.79 8 4" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">Daily backups</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Automated daily backups with point-in-time restoration. If something goes wrong, we roll back in minutes, not days.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:4">
          <div class="text-amber-400 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 19v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2zm0 0V9a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v10m-6 0a2 2 0 002 2h2a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h2a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2h-2a2 2 0 01-2-2z" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">Uptime monitoring</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Checked every 60 seconds. If your site goes down, I know about it before your customers do.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:5">
          <div class="text-amber-400 mb-4">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 17v-2m3 2v-4m3 4v-6m2 10H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">Site Health Report</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Monthly report delivered on day one. What happened, what's next, and how performance compares. The proof that the work gets done.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tiers -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Pricing</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">Pick your level.</h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 mt-4 max-w-2xl">Priced by site complexity. Pages, integrations, and traffic. All tiers include everything above. Multi-site discounts available.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 reveal-stagger" id="tier-cards">
        <!-- Good -->
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8 flex flex-col" style="--i:0">
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Good</p>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-2xl font-medium mb-1">Essentials</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm mb-6">For sites that need reliable hosting and someone watching.</p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-400 text-sm space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Managed cloud hosting
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Security & SSL
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Core & plugin updates
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Daily backups
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Uptime monitoring
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Monthly Site Health Report
            </li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-white/10 text-neutral-300 font-medium text-sm rounded-lg hover:border-white/25 hover:text-neutral-100 transition-all duration-300">
            Get started
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Better (recommended) -->
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8 flex flex-col ring-1 ring-amber-500/30 relative" style="--i:1">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-8 px-3 py-1 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 text-xs font-semibold rounded-full">
            Recommended
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Better</p>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-2xl font-medium mb-1">Professional</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm mb-6">For businesses that depend on their site to generate leads.</p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-400 text-sm space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Everything in Essentials
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              More included hours
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Quarterly performance reporting
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Content updates & minor edits
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Performance optimization
            </li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
            Get started
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Best -->
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-8 flex flex-col" style="--i:2">
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Best</p>
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-2xl font-medium mb-1">Priority</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm mb-6">For sites where downtime costs real money.</p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-400 text-sm space-y-3 mb-8 flex-1">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Everything in Professional
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Same-day priority response
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Maximum included hours
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Training included
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              Dedicated monthly call
            </li>
          </ul>
          <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-white/10 text-neutral-300 font-medium text-sm rounded-lg hover:border-white/25 hover:text-neutral-100 transition-all duration-300">
            Get started
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Questions</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">Common questions.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 reveal-stagger">
        <details class="reveal group glow-card" style="--i:0">
          <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between text-neutral-100 font-medium">
            What happens to my current hosting?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-500 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Your site moves to my infrastructure. Once everything's verified and running, you cancel your old hosting. I handle the full migration. DNS, files, database, email routing. Zero downtime.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="reveal group glow-card" style="--i:1">
          <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between text-neutral-100 font-medium">
            Do I still have access to my site?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-500 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Absolutely. You keep full WordPress admin access. Log in, edit content, publish posts, whatever you need. I handle the infrastructure and the stuff that requires technical knowledge.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="reveal group glow-card" style="--i:2">
          <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between text-neutral-100 font-medium">
            What if I want to leave?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-500 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            It's month-to-month after onboarding. No lock-in. If you leave, I'll give you a full backup and 30 days to migrate elsewhere. Your site is always yours.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="reveal group glow-card" style="--i:3">
          <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between text-neutral-100 font-medium">
            What about my domain and email?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-500 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Your domain stays yours. I never take ownership. Email routing is preserved during migration. If you're on shared hosting email, I'll help you set up something proper that won't break when the hosting changes.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="reveal group glow-card" style="--i:4">
          <summary class="p-6 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between text-neutral-100 font-medium">
            Do maintenance hours roll over?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-500 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            They don't. Hours are use-it-or-lose-it each month. Keeps pricing predictable for both of us. If you consistently need more, we'll adjust your tier. Consistently need fewer, same thing.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative py-32 px-6 surface-1 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[500px] h-[300px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-6">Ready to move your site?</h2>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg mb-10">Tell me what you're running and I'll tell you what the migration looks like.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="reveal inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
